Stock price project¶

  1. Data Preparation:

  • I use the MSCI data set of 6 developed countries: US, UK, Japan, Germany, France and Canada at https://www.msci.com/end-of-day-data-country

  • Data frequencies: monthly and annual.

  • Date length: full sample (possibly from 1969).

  • Currency domination: USD.

  • Size: Standard.

  1. I clean data by removing NA valuesa then calculate returns for each series in the data set. I then use matplotlib and seaborn package to produce plot of the above data set in two frequencies of monthly and annual levels as well as at both price and return levels and provide summary statistics of the data.

  2. I perform Cointegration Test as follows:

  • Using the Engle – Grangle 2 – step method to detect for any possible cointegration between the US and each of the other 5 countries.

  • Using the Johansen technique to detect for any possible cointegration among the 6 countries.

  • Note: for the cointergration checking I follow the full procedure from Checking order of integration for each series, VAR lag length selection, estimation of long-run equation using VAR and short-run VECM and report any necessary statistics and comments.

# Iterate over each file
for file_name in file_list:
 # Create the file path
 file_path = os.path.join(folder_path, file_name)
 # Read the file, skipping the first 7 rows and selecting the desired columns
 monthly = pd.read_excel(file_path, skiprows=6, usecols="A:B", nrows=641)
 # Remove rows with NaN values
 monthly = monthly.dropna()
 # Rename the columns to "Date" and "Price"
 monthly.columns = ["Date", "Price"]
 # Convert the "Price" column to numeric values
 monthly["Price"] = pd.to_numeric(monthly["Price"], errors="coerce")
 # Convert the "Date" column to datetime values
 monthly["Date"] = pd.to_datetime(monthly["Date"], errors="coerce")
 # Set the "Date" column as the index
 monthly.set_index("Date", inplace=True)
 # Replace non-numeric values with NaN
 monthly["Price"] = monthly["Price"].mask(pd.to_numeric(monthly["Price"], errors="coerce").isna())
 # Extract the country name from the file name
 country_name = file_name[:-5]
 # Concatenate the country's price column to the DataFrame
 all_monthly_price = pd.concat([all_monthly_price, monthly["Price"]], axis=1)
 all_monthly_price.rename(columns={"Price": country_name}, inplace=True)
 # Convert monthly data to yearly data
 yearly = monthly.resample('Y').mean()
 # Calculate returns
 monthly["Returns"] = monthly["Price"].pct_change()
 yearly["Returns"] = yearly["Price"].pct_change()
 all_monthly_return = pd.concat([all_monthly_return, monthly["Returns"]], axis=1)
 all_monthly_return.rename(columns={"Returns": country_name}, inplace=True)
 all_yearly_return = pd.concat([all_yearly_return, yearly["Returns"]], axis=1)
 all_yearly_return.rename(columns={"Returns": country_name}, inplace=True)
 # Summary statistics
 print("Summary statistics of " + str(file_name[:-5]) + " monthly price:" + "\n" + str(monthly['Price'].describe()) + "\n")
 print("Summary statistics of " + str(file_name[:-5]) + " monthly returns:" + "\n" + str(monthly['Returns'].describe()) + "\n")
 print("Summary statistics of " + str(file_name[:-5]) + " yearly price:" + "\n" + str(yearly['Price'].describe()) + "\n")
 print("Summary statistics of " + str(file_name[:-5]) + " yearly returns:" + "\n" + str(yearly['Returns'].describe()) + "\n")
 # Store the data in respective lists
 monthly_price.append(monthly["Price"])
 monthly_returns.append(monthly["Returns"])
 yearly_price.append(yearly["Price"])
 yearly_returns.append(yearly["Returns"])
 
# Remove rows with NaN values
all_monthly_return = all_monthly_return.dropna()
all_yearly_return = all_yearly_return.dropna()

# Engle–Grangle 2–step method to detect cointegration between the US ang others
us_price = monthly_price[0]
other_price = monthly_price[1:]
for i, country_price in enumerate(other_price):
    # Perform cointegration test
    result = coint(us_price, country_price)
    print("Cointegration test result for {} and US:".format(file_list[i + 1][:-5]))
    print("===================================")
    print("Test statistic: ", result[0])
    print("P-value: ", result[1])
    print("Critical values: ", result[2])
    if result[1] < 0.05:
        print("Cointegration detected between {} and US.".format(file_list[i + 1][:-5]) + "\n")
    else:
        print("No cointegration detected between {} and US.".format(file_list[i + 1][:-5]) + "\n")

# Kolmogorov-Smirnov test
for file_name in file_list:
     country_name = file_name[:-5]
     # Perform Kolmogorov-Smirnov test on monthly returns
     ks_statistic, ks_pvalue = stats.kstest(all_monthly_return[country_name], 'norm')
     print(f"Kolmogorov-Smirnov Test - Monthly Returns ({country_name}):")
     print(f"KS Statistic: " + str(ks_statistic))
     print(f"P-value: " + str(ks_pvalue))
     print(ks_pvalue < 0.01)
     print("")
     # Perform Kolmogorov-Smirnov test on yearly returns
     ks_statistic, ks_pvalue = stats.kstest(all_yearly_return[country_name], 'norm')
     print(f"Kolmogorov-Smirnov Test - Monthly Returns ({country_name}):")
     print(f"KS Statistic: " + str(ks_statistic))
     print(f"P-value: " + str(ks_pvalue))
     print(ks_pvalue < 0.01)
     print("")

# STATIONARY TEST

     print('p-value: %f' % station[1])

             print(f" {key}: {value}")

             print(f"There is evidence of cointegration between {country1} and {country2}")

             print(f"There is no evidence of cointegration between {country1} and {country2}")

# Johansen test
print("JOHANSEN TEST")
# Perform Johansen's Test of Cointegration for each pair of countries (yearly data)
for i in range(len(file_list)):
     for j in range(i + 1, len(file_list)):
         country1 = file_list[i][:-5]
         country2 = file_list[j][:-5]
         # Select the yearly returns for the pair of countries
         pair_yearly_returns = all_yearly_return[[country1, country2]]
         # Perform Johansen's test
         result = coint_johansen(pair_yearly_returns, det_order=0, k_ar_diff=1)
         print(f"Johansen's Test - {country1} and {country2}")
         print(f"Eigenvalues:")
         for eigenvalue in result.eig:
             print(f" {eigenvalue}")
         print(f"Trace Statistic:")
         for trace_stat in result.lr1:
             print(f" {trace_stat}")
         print(f"Critical Values (90% Confidence Level):")
         for key, value in zip(['0%', '5%', '10%'], result.cvt[:, 0]):
             print(f" {key}: {value}")
         # Check if there is cointegration
         rank = result.evec.shape[1]
         if rank > 0:
             print(f"Cointegration Rank: {rank}")
             print(f"There is evidence of cointegration between {country1} and {country2}")
         else:
             print(f"Cointegration Rank: 0")
             print(f"There is no evidence of cointegration between {country1} and {country2}")
         print("")

if rate < len(file_list) and rate > 0:
    # Cointegration exists case
    print("Cointegration exists among the variables.")
    print("The variables are non-stationary, and the number of cointegrating relationships is equal to", rate)
    print("Apply VECM to analyze short-run coefficients and long-run equilibrium/cointegration relationship.")
    
    # Perform VECM
    model_vecm = VECM(all_yearly_return, k_ar_diff=6, coint_rank=2, deterministic="co")
    results_vecm = model_vecm.fit()
    
    print("VECM Results - Short-run coefficients and Long-run equilibrium relationship:")
    print(results_vecm.summary())

    # Form equation for VECM
    coef_shortrun = results_vecm.gamma
    coef_longrun = results_vecm.beta
    coef_loading = results_vecm.alpha
    variables = results_vecm.names
    eq1 = {}
    
    for i in range(0, 6):
        equation1 = ""
        y = coef_shortrun[i]
        reshaped_y = np.reshape(y, (6, -1))
        equation1 += "Δ^" + variables[i] + " = "
        equation1 += str(results_vecm.const[i][0]) + " + "
        
        for j in range(0, 6):
            L = "Δ" + ".L" + str(j + 1) + "."
            
            for k in range(0, 6):
                var = variables[k]
                coef = reshaped_y[j][k]
                equation1 += str(coef) + str(L) + str(var) + " + "
        
        equation1 = equation1[:-3]
        eq1[file_list[i]] = equation1

    for i in range(0, 6):
        equation2 = ""
        ec1 = coef_loading[i][0]
        equation2 += str(ec1) + " * " + "("

        for j in range(0, 6):
            var = variables[j]
            if j != i:
                beta_ec1 = coef_longrun[j][0]
                equation2 += str(beta_ec1) + "." + str(var) + " + "
        
        equation2 = equation2[:-3]
        equation2 += ")"
        eq1[file_list[i]] += " + " + equation2

    for i in range(0, 6):

        for j in range(0, 6):
